news.title: Will object to Supertech move to build houses on site of twin towers: Emerald Court residents' body
news.para: The nearly 100-metre-tall twin towers -- Apex and Ceyane -- were demolished on August 28 in compliance with a landmark Supreme Court order that found their construction within Emerald Court premises in violation of norms.

news.title: Lodha Group repays offshore bonds worth $55 million ahead of scheduled maturity
news.para: The Lodha Group has repaid the bonds worth Rs 438 crore listed on the Singapore Exchange Securities Trading through its wholly owned subsidiary Lodha Developers International Ltd, Mauritius.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body officials recover property tax dues from eight owners
news.para: ​​They recovered dues from eight while one workshop was sealed and one building owner sought time till Monday.

news.title: Telangana HC stays land acquisition, move on oustees under lens
news.para: The judge made this interim order after hearing a petition filed by Cheruku Srinivas Reddy of Mutrajpally who questioned the process because it will take away his five-acre land in the village.

news.title: Base map for third master plan for Chennai yet to be prepared
news.para: The map, which will include information about the various zones, water bodies, roads, residential colonies, commercial establishments and other infrastructure, will help prepare the land-use plan and formulate strategies for the Chennai Metropolitan Area (CMA) area for the next few decades.

news.title: Nagpur civic body's operator starts collecting construction waste
news.para: The operator — Hyderabad C&D Waste Pvt Ltd — has conducted a survey and started to lift C&D waste from areas in Laxmi Nagar Zone. The NMC has provided 5 acre land to the operator for setting up the recycling plant, storage etc.

news.title: Lucknow, nearby areas to be developed as Uttar Pradesh state capital region
news.para: In a meeting with senior officials of the housing and urban planning department, Awas Vikas Parishad and all urban development authorities, the CM said that this area should include places like Unnao, Sitapur, Rae Bareli, Barabanki, Kanpur Nagar and Kanpur Dehat.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board allottee must remove all building violations first
news.para: CHB CEO Yashpal Garg, in an order issued on August 31, held that the aspects that unauthorized construction or misuse is on record and proceeding for cancellation are underway cannot be ignored in allowing conversion and conveyance deed.

news.title: NA land process for urban areas to be simplified: Maharashtra Deputy CM
news.para: Stating that citizens in urban areas have to make rounds of government offices to seek NA certificates, Fadnavis said the state revenue department will soon evaluate how to simplify the process and work out a system to do away with NA certificates.

news.title: Nagpur development body collects Rs 1 crore from EWS for PMAY registration
news.para: Alleging injustice towards poor people, former mayor Dayashankar Tiwari has pointed out this yet another major flaw in auction of flats by NMRDA.

news.title: Many IT buildings stand on stormwater drains: Karnataka minister
news.para: "The problem of flooding is more in areas where many IT companies are located. This is because these buildings are built on SWDs, which obstruct free flow of rainwater. The irony is owners of these buildings are venting their ire against the government," Basavaraj said.

news.title: RWA can use part of property tax for development work after achieving 'zero waste' status: MCD
news.para: ​The development work will be carried out by the MCD once the application for the incentive is cleared by the civic body, he said.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Illegal structures in Ramprastha, Surya Nagar to be razed
news.para: In fact, the petitioner, Kaushal Yadav, had approached the high court after coming across illegal construction in the Ramprastha area.

news.title: DDA plans to hand over first batch of flats in Kalkaji Extension & Kathputli Colony this month
news.para: While the first lot of 720 flats will be handed over to Kathputli Colony residents this month itself, 1,575 flats at Kalkaji Extension have already been allotted and possession letters are expected to be issued soon.

news.title: Gurugram civic body sees 66% jump in stamp duty earnings in Apr-Aug 2022
news.para: The civic body has earned Rs 123 crore from stamp duty between April 1 and August 31 - a large hike from the Rs 74.3 crore collected in these five months in 2021.
